  <prompt>Add `CustomDataSchemaConformanceTests.cs` in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/`. Test fixtures cover all 7 playbook output shapes asserting: AC-6a (enriched fields present), AC-6b (backward compat — old + new shape parse), AC-6c (payload &lt;10KB), AC-6d (every produced notification has sprk_category populated), AC-10 (all 7 playbooks emit schema-conformant output), AC-11 (unmappable Contact triggers member_skipped event — mock ILogger). Mock `IMembershipResolverService` for the AC-11 case.</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. xUnit test author following SPAARKE patterns (`.claude/patterns/testing/unit-test-structure.md`).</role>

  <goal>`tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Nodes/CustomDataSchemaConformanceTests.cs` exists with passing fixtures covering AC-6a/b/c/d, AC-10, AC-11. Tests pass on `dotnet test`. Failure modes are clear (assertion messages name the violated AC).</goal>

  <context>
    <background>R4 spec FR-10 AC-10 explicitly requires "test fixture passes asserting customData schema conformance for fixtures from all 7 playbooks". This task lands that fixture plus extends it to cover AC-6a/b/c/d (enriched customData + sprk_category column + payload size) and AC-11 (member_skipped event). Mock the `IMembershipResolverService` to exercise both happy-path (SystemUser-mapped contact) and unmappable-contact (NULL azureactivedirectoryobjectid) cases. Use the existing test model `CreateNotificationNodeExecutorTests.cs` as a structural template.</background>
