  <steps>
    <step order="1">Load knowledge files. Re-read AC-6a/b/c/d, AC-10, AC-11. Read the existing `CreateNotificationNodeExecutorTests.cs` for structural pattern.</step>
    <step order="2">Author `CustomDataSchemaConformanceTests.cs`. Class with private helpers: `MakeExecutor(IMembershipResolverService? mockResolver = null, ILogger&lt;...&gt;? mockLogger = null)`, `MakeFixtureInput(string playbookCode, bool withMatterLinkage = true, int membershipRoleCount = 1)`, `ExtractCustomDataJson(Entity notification)`.</step>
    <step order="3">Test 1 (AC-6a): For each of 7 playbook codes, assert `BuildNotificationEntity` output's customData JSON contains keys: category, priority, actionUrl, dueDate, regardingName, regardingEntityType, regardingId, viaMatter (when withMatterLinkage=true), source. Use Theory + InlineData per playbook.</step>
    <step order="4">Test 2 (AC-6b backward compat): Round-trip the enriched customData through a JSON deserializer matching the widget's old shape contract — verify the existing 4 fields (category, priority, actionUrl, dueDate) still parse correctly. Then deserialize via the new shape — verify both.</step>
    <step order="5">Test 3 (AC-6c): Serialize the enriched customData JSON to bytes; assert byte-length &lt; 10240 (10KB ceiling). Use a fixture with realistic multi-membership data to stress the upper bound.</step>
    <step order="6">Test 4 (AC-6d): Assert produced Entity has `sprk_category` attribute set, and its value equals customData.category.</step>
    <step order="7">Test 5 (AC-10): Loop over 7 playbook fixtures — assert all conform to schema. This is essentially Test 1 packaged as a single sanity-check that exercises all 7 codes.</step>
    <step order="8">Test 6 (AC-11): Construct a fixture matter with a Contact member whose azureactivedirectoryobjectid is NULL. Mock IMembershipResolverService + ILogger via Moq. Invoke LookupUserMembershipNodeExecutor (or MembershipResolverService — whichever task 027 chose). Verify `mockLogger.Verify(...)` was called once with LogLevel.Warning + a state-formatter containing "member_skipped" + the 4 fields. Assert exact field values.</step>
    <step order="9">Test 7 (AC-6a viaMatter omission): Fixture with no matter linkage — assert viaMatter key is absent from customData JSON (not present-as-null).</step>
    <step order="10">Test 8 (AC-6a multi-role): Fixture with 2 memberships (owner + assignedAttorney) — assert viaMatter.memberships is array length 2 with both role entries.</step>
    <step order="11">Run `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter FullyQualifiedName~CustomDataSchemaConformanceTests` — fix failures.</step>
    <step order="12">Run full suite `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` to confirm no regression elsewhere.</step>
    <step order="13">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: change task 028 status to ✅.</step>
    <step order="14">Document any test gaps or skipped cases in `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service-r4/notes/`.</step>
  </steps>

